<dl id="n06130a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06130a">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06130a"> 130(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> at once found seriousness / of what I had done <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06130a"><li>FW 72.29 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06130a">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06130a">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06130a">MS BL 47471b-8v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:161 <a name="c30d" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#c30d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c30d.htm#n06130a">Draft: I.3&sect;3.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Dans la suite, quand je lus la Vie de Spinoza par Colerus, je vis que j&apos;avais eu sous les yeux dans mon enfance un mod&egrave;le tout semblable au saint d&apos;Amsterdam. On le laissait tout &agrave; fait tranquille; on le <font color="green">[107]</font> respectait m&ecirc;me. Sa r&eacute;signation, sa mine souriante, paraissaient une vision d&apos;un autre monde. On ne comprenait pas, mais on sentait en lui quelque chose de sup&eacute;rieur; <br><font color="green">[Later, when I read Spinoza&apos;s Life by Colerus, I saw that I had seen in my childhood a model very similar to the Saint of Amsterdam. He was left perfectly calm; he was respected even. His resignation, his smiling face, seemed a vision of another world. One did not understand, but one felt in him something superior;]</font> <small> Ernest Renan, <a name="ERSD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ERSD"><cite title="source">Souvenirs d'enfance et de jeunesse</cite></a> (1883) ?107f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
